Created Jassm _(just another static site maker<sup>1</sup>)_, a lightweight abstraction layer over MDX and React for building router-agnostic,
content-driven websites such as blogs and documentation platforms focused on simplyfing process for both developers and Authors alike.

It is built around a registry-based architecture powered by Vite’s `import.meta.glob`,
which allows automatic discovery of _pages_ and their respective bundled metadata and exports.

## Key Features

### A Type-Safe content registry

- Uses vite's `import.meta.glob` to construct a filesystem-based registry of pages.
- Ensures compile time type safe static path accesses.
- The registry system further allows for a predictable and strongly typed access to exports and page metadata without any manual imports.

### Implicit Component Injection into MDX at Runtime

_Components_ are registered globally once and are automatically injecting into the rendered MDX component at runtime. Which eliminates the need for manual importing within the source files.

### CSS Class-Map Based Styling System

Style classes are linked externally via a key value map, which decouples the stylings from core components and allows the usage of any framework and method for styling components.

### Simple Authoring Process

The system is structured as such that it provides a separation of concern between developers and content creators wherein adding new pages is as simple as creating its corresponding file in the source directory.

### Lazy Loading content

Each MDX route is loaded lazily only when requested, this provides inifinite scalability
